{{Multiple issues | Refimprove = December 2023 | Original research = December 2023 }} {{Infobox deity | name = Yakine no Mikoto | type = [[Kunitsukami|Kunitsukami]] | full_name = 八杵命 (Yakine no Mikoto) | other_names = | alternate_names = | Rank = | divine_role = God of cultivation and development | burial_place = Traditions exist | father = [[Takeminakata-no-Kami]] | mother = [[Yasakatome-no-Kami]] | spouse = | children = [[Kurusu no Kami]], [[Hirahuo no Kami]], [[Wakaname no Kami]], [[Yatate no Kami]], [[Ōanamuchi|Kuraokami no Kami]] | shrines = [[Suwa Taisha]], [[Yagi Shrine]] | related_clans = [[Koide clan (Negi Daibu)|Koide clan]] }}
'''Yakine no Mikoto''' (八杵命, also read as Yaki no Mikoto) is a deity from the folk traditions of the [[Suwa region]] in [[Nagano Prefecture]], associated with the [[Suwa Faith]] (諏訪信仰). He is revered as a god of development and cultivation.
== Overview == Yakine no Mikoto is mentioned in historical sources such as the {{ill|Genealogy of the Deities|ja|神氏系図|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. He is described as a child of {{ill|Takeminakata-no-Kami|ja|建御名方神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, but little is recorded beyond his lineage and descendants. The deity is regarded as the ancestral god of the {{ill|Koide clan (Negi Daibu)|ja|小出氏|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, who served as the '''Negi Daibu''' (禰宜大夫), one of the {{ill|Five Priestly Offices|ja|五官祝|qq=draft|qq=draft}} of [[Suwa Taisha]]'s Upper Shrine. However, no detailed genealogical records exist, leaving much of his story shrouded in mystery.
At [[Yagi Shrine]] in [[Shimosuwa, Nagano|Shimosuwa]], Yakine no Mikoto is venerated as a god of development in the historical [[Shinano Province]]. Local lore claims that his burial site is located nearby, but the exact location is unknown.
== Interpretations == Yakine no Mikoto does not appear in other historical texts, and it is uncertain whether shrines dedicated to him exist outside Nagano Prefecture. Some theories equate him with {{ill|Yahoko no Kami|ja|八桙神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, the deity enshrined at [[Yahoko Shrine]], an ancient {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in [[Awa Province]].
== Lineage == Yakine no Mikoto is one of the children of {{ill|Takeminakata-no-Kami|ja|建御名方神|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Yasakatome-no-Kami|ja|八坂刀売神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. His offspring include: * [[Kurusu no Kami]] * [[Hirahuo no Kami]] * [[Wakaname no Kami]] * [[Yatate no Kami]] (also known as Hachitama no Kami) * [[Ōanamuchi|Kuraokami no Kami]] (倉稲主神, also known as Kuraokami)
== Shrines == Yakine no Mikoto is venerated at the following locations: * [[Suwa Taisha]] Upper Shrine - {{ill|Wakamiya Shrine|ja|若御子社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Chino City, Nagano Prefecture) * Suwa Taisha Lower Shrine - {{ill|Wakamiya Shrine|ja|若宮社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Shimosuwa, Nagano Prefecture) * [[Yagi Shrine]] (Shimosuwa, Nagano Prefecture)
